    <h1>About Vancouver</h1>
    <h2>Getting Around</h2>
    <p>
      We both love Vancouver and we are very excited by this opportunity to share it with you. It has something for
      everyone! The easiest way to get around the city is to use public transit like the buses and Skytrains. If that's
      not your thing, we also have taxis. Like any major city, all of Vancouver's transit options are
      <%= link_to 'available on Google Maps', 'https://www.google.com/maps', :target => '_blank' %>, so plan your trips there.
    </p>
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-md-4">
        <h1>
          <small class="subtitle"><b>Skytrain</b></small>
        </h1>
        <p>
          There are several other lines, but the Canada line is the one you'll use most while you're here.
          It travels from the airport to Waterfront Station in downtown Vancouver.
        </p>
        <a href="http://www.translink.ca/-/media/Documents/schedules_and_maps/transit_maps/SkyTrainSystemMap.pdf" target="_blank" class="btn">Skytrain Map</a>
      </div>
      <div class="col-md-4">
        <h1>
          <small class="subtitle"><b>Bus</b></small>
        </h1>
        <p>Buses are cheap and easy to use. They stop every couple blocks and allow you to transfer to
          other buses, skytrains, or even the <%= link_to 'Seabus', 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/SeaBus', :target => '_blank' %> if you want to explore the
          <%= link_to 'North Shore', 'http://vancouversnorthshore.com/things-to-do/', :target => '_blank' %>.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="col-md-4">
